summary: An email from an individual apologizing for a filing error regarding a declaration in the case Times v. B01 3, 20-cv-833, where the declaration was initially filed without exhibits and then re-filed with them, resulting in two docket entries.

events.title: Declaration Filing Error
events.description: A declaration was initially filed without exhibits in Times v. B01 3, 20-cv-833, and then re-filed with exhibits, creating two docket entries.

keyFacts: A filing error occurred in the case Times v. B01 3, 20-cv-833, where a declaration was filed twice: once without exhibits and once with exhibits.
The error was communicated via email on August 6, 2020, with an offer to submit a letter to the Court explaining the mistake.
The email sender experienced a remote login lockout shortly after the filings were made.
